HEADWORD: Nehushtan
<hw>Ne*hush"tan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.]</ety>
<def>A thing of brass; -- the name under which the Israelites worshiped
the brazen serpent made by Moses.</def> <rj><au>2 Kings xviii.
4.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
